  "buggy_files": ["drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["iwl_hw_card_ids"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug report describes missing PCI subdevice entries for device ID 0x2526 (Intel Wireless-AC 9260) with subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C. In drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c, the iwl_hw_card_ids array contains entries for 0x2526 with various subdevice IDs (e.g., 0x4034, 0x40A4, 0x4234, 0x42A4), but is missing entries for 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C. These missing entries cause the firmware to not be loaded for cards with those subdevice IDs, as they fall through to the catch-all PCI_ANY_ID entry with a base transport config instead of the proper 9260 config. The fix would add IWL_PCI_DEVICE(0x2526, 0x4010, ...), IWL_PCI_DEVICE(0x2526, 0x4018, ...), and IWL_PCI_DEVICE(0x2526, 0x401C, ...) entries with the appropriate iwl9260 configuration."
}

